cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper discusses a distributed caching scheme for cellular networks, which involves optimizing the transmission cost of the network. This topic is related to several sub-categories of computer science, including networked systems (cs.NI), distributed computing (cs.DC), information theory (cs.IT), control systems (cs.SY), and multimedia (cs.MM). However, given the focus on cellular networks and caching, cs.NI and cs.DC are the most likely sub-categories. The use of optimization algorithms and analysis of system parameters also suggest cs.IT and cs.SY as possible sub-categories. Finally, the consideration of file popularity distribution and the potential impact on multimedia content delivery suggest cs.MM as a less likely but still possible sub-category.
